"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426647","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-17","<p>As quoted in the Public Accounts Committee report (attached below), the bulk of legacy claims will be transferred by the end of 2019.</p><p><a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201415/cmselect/cmpubacc/810/81002.htm" target="_blank">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201415/cmselect/cmpubacc/810/81002.htm</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-11-17T15:23:28.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426647/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426647/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426647/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-05","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the number of people who will be in receipt of legacy benefits and awaiting transfer to universal credit in May 2020.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","15083"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426648","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-10","<p>Administration has been assumed to be the Departmental Expenditure Limit Administrative spend and has been taken from the Department’s Annual Report and Accounts for 2014/15 (Table 4, page 184).</p><br /><p>The information that is available is in the table below:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p>The Department for Work and Pensions spent the following amounts: <br> <br> <table><tbody><tr><td><p><br></p></td><td><p>Temporary Agency Staff £m</p></td><td><p>Consultants £m</p></td><td><p>Administration £m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>30.8</p></td><td><p>14.3</p></td><td><p>5,610</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>11.5</p></td><td><p>8.7</p></td><td><p>1,333</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>12.6</p></td><td><p>8.4</p></td><td><p>1,180</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>13.1</p></td><td><p>11.7</p></td><td><p>1,091</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>31.1</p></td><td><p>10.5</p></td><td><p>894</p></td></tr></tbody></table></p></td></tr></tbody></table> <br /><p>Information on marketing and advertising costs could only be provided at disproportionate cost. To put this into context, the cost of temporary agency staff was just over 1% of the Department’s paybill in 2014-15.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-11-10T17:11:35.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426648/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426648/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426648/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-05","Department for Work and Pensions: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much his Department has spent on (a) temporary agency staff, (b) consultants, (c) non-payroll staff, (d) administration and (e) marketing and advertising in real terms in each year since 2010-11.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","15151"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426649","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-10","<p>The Government believes that local authorities are best placed to provide for the care needs of people in their local community. The Care Act 2014 introduced stringent minimum standards for this care and it is within this context that local authorities took over responsibility for the care and support of former Independent Living Fund users from 1st July 2015.</p><p>The government has fully-funded them to meet their additional obligations for the remainder of the 2015/16 financial year, but does not hold information on the care packages of individual former users. It has, however, committed to conducting research on the impact of the Fund’s closure and has already identified a sample of former users who have agreed to participate.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-11-10T14:40:27.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426649/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426649/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426649/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-05","Independent Living Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in receipt of the independent living fund have had that funding reduced following the transfer of that fund to local authorities.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","15140"
