"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426053","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-11-17","<p>Revealing negotiations regarding prisoner transfer agreements can be counterproductive given their sensitivity. My Ministerial colleagues and I are actively engaging with a number of countries and remain determined to secure compulsory agreements wherever possible. Currently the UK has over 100 prisoner transfer agreements with other countries and territories.</p>",,"Lord Faulks",,"2015-11-17T12:51:22.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426053/answer","Biography information for Lord Faulks","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426053/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426053/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-11-04","Prisoners: Repatriation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government with which countries the UK is currently negotiating prisoner transfer agreements.","false","Biography information for Lord Falconer of Thoroton",,"Lord Falconer of Thoroton","HL3326"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426054","Home Office","false","2015-11-19","<p>The minimum salary threshold for Tier 2 (General) rises annually in line with UK wage inflation. It was £20,300 from 2013/14, £20,500 in 2014/15 and £20,800 in 2015/16. Additionally, for a Certificate of Sponsorship to be allocated, the employer (the sponsor) must be paying the appropriate salary rate for the occupation in question. These rates are set out in Appendix J of the Immigration Rules: https://www.gov.uk/guidance/immigration-rules/immigration-rules-appendix-j-codes-of-practice-for-skilled-work.</p><p>Restricted Certificates of Sponsorship are subject to an annual limit and are allocated to sponsoring employers each month. The limit was undersubscribed until June 2015 and so all valid applications for Restricted Certificates of Sponsorship were granted, where the salary was at least equal to the minimum thresholds above.</p><p>If the limit is oversubscribed, as it has been since June, applications for Restricted Certificates of Sponsorship are prioritised using a points table. Points are awarded for shortage occupations, PhD-level occupations, and salary. The minimum salaries for successful applications since June are shown in the table below:</p><table><tbody><tr><td rowspan="2"><p>Month</p></td><td colspan="3"><p>Minimum salary for successful applications</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Shortage occupations</p></td><td><p>PhD-level occupations</p></td><td><p>Other occupations</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>June 2015</p></td><td><p>£20,800</p></td><td><p>£20,800</p></td><td><p>£46,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>July 2015</p></td><td><p>£20,800</p></td><td><p>£20,800</p></td><td><p>£32,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>August 2015</p></td><td><p>£20,800</p></td><td><p>£20,800</p></td><td><p>£24,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>September 2015</p></td><td><p>£20,800</p></td><td><p>£20,800</p></td><td><p>£27,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>October 2015</p></td><td><p>£20,800</p></td><td><p>£20,800</p></td><td><p>£22,000</p></td></tr></tbody></table>",,"Lord Bates",,"2015-11-19T16:56:57.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426054/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426054/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426054/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-11-04","Visas","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what was the minimum salary required of a Tier 2 (General) visa applicant in order to be allocated a Certificate of Sponsorship in each of the last 24 months.","false","Biography information for Lord Green of Deddington",,"Lord Green of Deddington","HL3327"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426055","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-18","<p>The information requested is not held centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate cost. However, in July 2011 the Government put in place its Guiding Principles for EU Legislation, which state that the Government will not go beyond the minimum requirements of the measure which is being transposed, save in exceptional circumstances. Since the Guiding Principles have applied there have been only five instances of new “gold-plating” of EU Directives that have placed additional costs on business which is attached.</p><br /> <br />",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2015-11-18T17:25:48.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426055/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426055/answer","guiding-principles-for-eu-legislation.pdf","guiding-principles-for-eu-legislation.pdf","Guiding principles for EU Legislation","Guiding principles for EU Legislation","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426055/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-04","EU Law","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many EU directives have been transposed into UK law without any additional material being included since the coming into force of the Lisbon Treaty, and what percentage of the total number of directives transposed that number represents.","false","Biography information for Lord Inglewood",,"Lord Inglewood","HL3328"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426056","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-18","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley","HL3330","2015-11-18T16:09:27.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426056/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426056/answer","HL3329, HL3330 attachment.pdf","HL3329, HL3330 attachment.pdf","ONS attachment","ONS attachment","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426056/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-04","UK Trade with EU","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what percentage of UK exports are to the EU, excluding exports that go to the ports of Rotterdam and Antwerp before being transited to locations outside the EU.","false","Biography information for Lord Kilclooney",,"Lord Kilclooney","HL3329"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426057","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-18","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley","HL3329","2015-11-18T16:09:27.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426057/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426057/answer","HL3329, HL3330 attachment.pdf","HL3329, HL3330 attachment.pdf","ONS attachment","ONS attachment","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426057/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-04","UK Trade with EU","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the ONS Balance of Payments includes in its estimate of UK exports to the EU the wings manufactured in the UK for Airbus that are later exported outside the EU.","false","Biography information for Lord Kilclooney",,"Lord Kilclooney","HL3330"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426058","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-11-17","<p>The British Government deployed 2 Long Term Observers to join 18 other Long Term Observers in the Organisation for Security and Co-operation in Europe (OSCE) Office for Democratic Institutions and Human Rights Limited Election Observation Mission for the early parliamentary elections in Turkey on 1 November 2015.</p><p>Delegations from the Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe (PACE) and the Parliamentary Assembly of the OSCE also observed the elections in Turkey on 1 November.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-11-17T16:17:38.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426058/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426058/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426058/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-11-04","Turkey: Election Observers","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they participated in the election observer presences at the recent elections in Turkey; and whether OSCE or Council of Europe observer delegations were also present at those elections.","false","Biography information for Lord Kilclooney",,"Lord Kilclooney","HL3331"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426059","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-11-17","<p>The Organisation for Security and Co-operation in Europe Parliamentary Assembly decided not to send observers. However the Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe sent a 28 member observation team.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-11-17T16:17:50.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426059/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426059/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426059/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-11-04","Azerbaijan: Election Observers","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they participated in the election observer presence at the recent elections in Azerbaijan; and whether OSCE or Council of Europe observer delegations were also present at those elections.","false","Biography information for Lord Kilclooney",,"Lord Kilclooney","HL3332"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426060","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-11-17","<p>It is the long-standing policy of successive Governments not to comment in detail on matters of intelligence. This includes discussions with allies and liaison agencies.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-11-17T17:27:54.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426060/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426060/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426060/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-11-04","USA: Electronic Surveillance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they have discussed with the government of the United States the collection of UK citizens’ data through the PRISM programme, and if so, with what result.","false","Biography information for Lord Laird",,"Lord Laird","HL3333"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426061","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-11-17","<p>It is the long-standing policy of successive Governments not to comment in detail on matters of intelligence. This includes discussions with allies and liaison agencies.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-11-17T17:29:01.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426061/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426061/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426061/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-11-04","USA: Electronic Surveillance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the extent to which UK citizens’ data have been collected by the government of the United States through the PRISM programme, and whether they have taken steps to prevent such data being collected in the future.","false","Biography information for Lord Laird",,"Lord Laird","HL3334"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426062","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-11-12","<p>The Government remains in regular contact with the Irish Government relating to the Belfast Agreement in accordance with the established three-stranded approach.</p>",,"Lord Dunlop",,"2015-11-12T13:03:52.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426062/answer","Biography information for Lord Dunlop","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426062/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426062/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-11-04","Northern Ireland Government","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what process is in place to monitor the actions of the government of the Republic of Ireland relating to the 1998 Belfast Agreement.","false","Biography information for Lord Laird",,"Lord Laird","HL3335"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426063","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-11-18","<p>For those who bring discrimination cases, we have made sure fee waivers are available for those who cannot afford to pay. The Government is currently carrying out a post-implementation review of the introduction of fees in the Employment Tribunals. The review will report in due course and we will consult on any proposals for change in the usual way.</p>",,"Lord Faulks",,"2015-11-18T14:10:59.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426063/answer","Biography information for Lord Faulks","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426063/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426063/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-11-04","Maternity Leave: Discrimination","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of the research on maternity discrimination, <i>Pregnancy and Maternity – Related Discrimination and Disadvantage: First Findings</i>, estimating that up to 54,000 mothers leave their jobs each year because of maternity discrimination, what plans they have to exempt maternity discrimination cases from employment tribunal fees.","false","Biography information for Lord Lester of Herne Hill",,"Lord Lester of Herne Hill","HL3336"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426064","Department for Education","false","2015-11-16","<p>The government will await the final report on pregnancy and maternity discrimination and carefully consider any recommendations from the Equality and Human Rights Commission before deciding on next steps.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2015-11-16T16:42:30.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426064/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426064/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426064/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-11-04","Maternity Leave: Discrimination","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of the research on maternity discrimination, <i>Pregnancy and Maternity – Related Discrimination and Disadvantage: First Findings</i>, whether they will consider extending the time limit for bringing maternity discrimination claims before an employment tribunal from three to six months.","false","Biography information for Lord Lester of Herne Hill",,"Lord Lester of Herne Hill","HL3337"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426065","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-11-17","<p>A copy of the letter will be placed in the Library of the House.</p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2015-11-17T16:22:01.99Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426065/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426065/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426065/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-11-04","Cetaceans: Faroe Islands","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Gardiner of Kimble on 17 September (HL2164), whether they will place in the Library of the House a copy of the letter from the UK Commissioner to the International Whaling Commission to the governments of Denmark and the Faroe Islands about concerns over the welfare and sustainability of their hunts.","false","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Goss Moor",,"Lord Taylor of Goss Moor","HL3338"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426066","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-18","<p>Kids Company delivered important work for vulnerable young people and received support from successive governments over a 15 year period, beginning in 2002.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley",,"2015-11-18T16:08:21.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426066/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426066/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426066/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-04","Kids Company","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their assessment of the value for money of the estimated £46 million of public funds provided to Kids Company over the last 15 years.","false","Biography information for Lord Truscott",,"Lord Truscott","HL3339"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426070","Department of Health","false","2015-11-11","<p>There is no fixed chair of the group. It rotates between the Department of Health, UNICEF and Public Health England (PHE).</p><br /><p>The members of the group are:</p><br /><p>Madeleine Percival – Department of Health</p><p>Bridget Halnan - Institute of Health Visitors</p><p>Dr Helen Duncan – PHE</p><p>Kate Thurland – PHE</p><p>Alison Burton – PHE</p><p>Francesca Entwhistle – National Infant Feeding Network</p><p>Sue Ashmore – UNICEF UK Baby Friendly Initiative</p><p>Viv Bennett – PHE</p><p>Sue Hatton – Health Education England (HEE)</p><p>Lisa Bayliss Pratt - HEE</p><br /><p>There is also a representative on the group from the Royal College of Midwives.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2015-11-11T09:40:22.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426070/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426070/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426070/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-04","National Infant Feeding Steering Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 19 October 2015 to Question 10790, who (a) the chair and (b) other members of the National Infant Feeding Steering Group are.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","14864"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426071","Department of Health","false","2015-11-11","<p>The minutes of the meetings are attached.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2015-11-11T11:28:19.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426071/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426071/answer","Breastfeeding System meeting 2014.docx ; Breastfeeding coordinators 2015.doc","Breastfeeding System meeting 2014.docx ; Breastfeeding coordinators 2015.doc","Meeting minutes 2014 ; Meeting minutes 2015","Meeting minutes 2014 ; Meeting minutes 2015","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426071/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-04","National Infant Feeding Steering Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 19 October 2015 to Question 10790, if he will place in the Library the minutes of meetings of the National Infant Feeding Steering Group in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","14865"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426072","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-10","<p>The UK has a strong record on nuclear disarmament. Since 1985 the WE 177 and Polaris warheads have been removed from operational service leaving only one type of nuclear warhead in service delivered by the Trident missile system. These withdrawals from operational service have been as a result of unilateral action. As my right hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Defence set out in his Written Ministerial Statement of 20 January 2015 (Official Report, column 4WS) the Government has met its commitment to implement the changes announced in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2010 to reduce the number of operationally available warheads from fewer than 160 to no more than 120.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-11-10T16:28:34.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426072/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426072/answer","20150120_WMS_Nuclear_Deterrent.docx","20150120_WMS_Nuclear_Deterrent.docx","20150120 - WMS Hansard extract - Nuclear Deterrent","20150120 - WMS Hansard extract - Nuclear Deterrent","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426072/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-04","Nuclear Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many UK nuclear weapons have been withdrawn from operational service as a result of (a) multilateral negotiation and (b) unilateral action since 1985.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","14817"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426073","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-11-10","<p>The causes of the delays at Olkiluoto 3 include complex contractual structures and a series of design changes suggested by the local regulator after the start of construction. Hinkley Point C will commence construction with a more mature design. Our different regulatory regime and improved contracting arrangements will ensure that issues will not arise in the UK.</p><br /><p>Flamanville 3 has experienced delays as a result of changes to the design after the start of construction, changes to regulatory requirements, including modifications to take account of lessons learned from the accident at Fukushima in 2011, and quality problems with key components. In the UK, responsibility for delivery and compliance with regulatory requirements lies with EDF and its co-investors. The shareholders in the project carry the full construction risk.</p><br /><p>EDF Energy, overseen by the UK’s Office for Nuclear Regulation, will apply any relevant lessons learned and ensure the delivery of high standards of nuclear safety for its new nuclear power plants in the UK.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-11-10T15:43:44.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426073/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426073/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426073/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-11-04","Nuclear Power Stations: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, pursuant to the Answer of 2 November 2015 to Question 13044, what the (a) technical, (b) regulatory and (c) contractual reasons were for delays at (i) Olkiluoto 3 and (ii) Flamanville 3 reactors.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","14863"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426074","Department of Health","false","2015-11-11","<p>Information on the number of standalone midwife-led units, midwife-led units situated alongside consultant-led units and consultant-led maternity units in each region of England is set out in the table below:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p><br></p></td><td><p>Standalone midwife-led units</p></td><td><p>Midwife-led units situated alongside consultant-led units</p></td><td><p>Consultant-led maternity units</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>North West, Lancashire, Cheshire, Merseyside</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>12</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Cumbria, North East of England and Yorkshire and the Humber</p></td><td><p>8</p></td><td><p>8</p></td><td><p>24</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>NHS Midlands and East. <br></p></td><td><p>14</p></td><td><p>37</p></td><td><p>44</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>South East Coast and Wessex</p></td><td><p>8</p></td><td><p>12</p></td><td><p>16</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>South</p></td><td><p>18</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>18</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>London</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>22</p></td><td><p>25</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>Women can expect a range of choices over place of birth. As set out in the NHS Choice Framework for 2015/16, these choices include giving birth at home with the support of a midwife, in a midwifery facility with the support of a midwife, or in any available hospital with the support of a maternity team. Choices will depend on what is best for the woman and her baby, as well as what is available locally.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2015-11-11T11:11:08.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426074/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426074/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426074/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-04","Maternity Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many NHS (a) standalone midwife-led units, (b) midwife-led units situated alongside consultant-led units and (c) consultant-led maternity units there are in each region of England; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","14850"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426075","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-11-12","<p>The BVI Government issued a public consultation document in November 2013, seeking public opinion on whether or not the BVI should adopt a central register of beneficial ownership. The consultation process concluded in March 2014 and this was followed by a review and analysis of the submissions. The results were published in February 2015. Since then the BVI Government has been working with the financial services industry to develop proposals which led to the Statement made by the Premier in the House of Assembly on 3 November on changes to the BVI Business Companies Act and Anti Money Laundering legislation. We will continue to work with the BVI authorities so that the changes to their systems meet the three criteria that the Government has set out.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2015-11-12T13:22:32.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426075/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426075/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426075/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-11-04","British Virgin Islands: Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the length of time it is taking the British Virgin Island government to respond to its consultation on a public register of beneficial ownership.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","14757"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426076","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-11-12","<p>In March the Financial Secretary to the Treasury and I wrote to the Premier of the British Virgin Islands asking him to set out plans and a timetable for the implementation of a central register of company beneficial ownership, or similarly effective system, ahead of the Joint Ministerial Council. The letter included three criteria we expect BVI to meet.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2015-11-12T13:19:44.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426076/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426076/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426076/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-11-04","British Virgin Islands: Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the steps taken by the British Virgin Islands to meet the Prime Minister's ambition for a public register of beneficial ownership since June 2013.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","14756"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426077","Department of Health","false","2015-11-09","<p>This information is not held centrally.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-11-09T15:38:39.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426077/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426077/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426077/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-04","Mental Health Services: Medical Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, on how many occasions patients were refused access to their mental health records in 2014.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","14972"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426078","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-11-09","<p>Reoffending had been too high for too long. Under the last government, we reformed the way offenders are managed in the community, so all offenders get support when they leave prison. We want to build on this to address what can be done whilst offenders are in prison, with a new emphasis on rehabilitation and redemption. Working with the voluntary, public and private sectors, we are helping offenders turn away from crime.</p><br /><p>Research and evidence of best practice is shared widely across the United Kingdom and we engage the Devolved Administrations on a wide range of offender issues. We will ensure that these discussions include examining the most effective measures for reducing reoffending.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-11-09T17:16:17.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426078/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426078/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426078/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-11-04","Reoffenders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will hold discussions with the devolved administrations on establishing best practice in reducing re-offending rates throughout the UK.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","14973"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426079","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-11-12","<p>We are aware of reports that elephants in use in the tourist industry in India have been captured as calves and then beaten and mistreated. This practice is illegal in India. UK officials have had discussions on this issue with Save The Asian Elephant (STAE).</p><p>The UK is committed to conserving Asian elephants and recognises the growing threats to their populations, including from the cross-border, illegal trade in live animals to feed the demand by the tourist and entertainment industries. The UK has been working internationally through the Convention on International Trade in Endangered Species (CITES) in discussion with elephant range states, including India, to increase protection for Asian elephants. We secured agreement in 2014 for elephant range states to put in place measures to prevent illegal trade in live elephants.</p><p>We are very much looking forward to Indian Prime Minister Modi’s visit, which gives us an opportunity to discuss a range of issues. We will continue to work together with the Indian authorities, as well as STAE and other non-governmental organisation, on protecting elephants.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2015-11-12T17:37:46.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426079/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426079/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426079/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-11-04","India: Elephants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will raise with the Prime Minister of India during his forthcoming visit the welfare of elephants being trained to work in the tourism industry in that country.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","14718"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426080","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-10","<p>The Government wants almost every car and van to be a zero emission vehicle by 2050 and is investing £500m between 2015 and 2020 to help deliver this. The long-term transition to ultra low emission vehicles can help improve local air quality, and will also lower UK greenhouse gas emissions and provide high value jobs and growth, but our modelling suggests that even very rapid uptake can have only a marginal impact on today’s air quality problems because of the time taken to turn over the vehicle fleet.</p><br /><p>We are aware that a number of local authorities have been assessing electric car charging point requirements in air quality management areas.</p><br /><p>The Government is considering future grid and chargepoint requirements as part of its planning for this transition. The UK already has the largest network of rapid chargepoints across Europe and over 6000 publically accessible chargepoints have been part-funded by the Government. We will continue to collaborate with industry to ensure that the UK’s infrastructure network meets the needs of electric vehicle drivers.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","14767","2015-11-10T17:30:02.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426080/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426080/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426080/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-04","Electric Vehicles: Charging Points","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the (a) number of electric charging points in air quality management areas, (b) number of such points needed to have an effect on air quality and (c) associated costs of upgrading the necessary grid infrastructure.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","14855"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426081","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-11-10","<p>While no formal assessment of the impact of LPG has been made by the Department, Defra officials met with representatives of the LPG industry during the consultation period for the draft UK Air Quality Plans.</p><br /><p>Industry data shows that retrofitting older diesel cars and vans to run on LPG can reduce emissions of NOx (oxides of nitrogen) and particulate matter whilst producing CO<sub>2</sub> (carbon dioxide) emissions between those of equivalent diesel and petrol engines. This solution was used by some drivers to enable them to enter the London Low Emission Zone without charge. Retrofitting to use LPG can also be a cheaper option for drivers than replacing their vehicle with a newer model.</p><br />","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2015-11-10T12:20:36.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426081/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426081/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426081/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-11-04","Motor Vehicles: Liquefied Petroleum Gas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment her Department has made of the role of LPG autogas in helping to improve urban air quality.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","14856"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426082","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-10","<p>The Government wants almost every car and van to be a zero emission vehicle by 2050 and is investing £500m between 2015 and 2020 to help deliver this. The long-term transition to ultra low emission vehicles can help improve local air quality, and will also lower UK greenhouse gas emissions and provide high value jobs and growth, but our modelling suggests that even very rapid uptake can have only a marginal impact on today’s air quality problems because of the time taken to turn over the vehicle fleet.</p><br /><p>We are aware that a number of local authorities have been assessing electric car charging point requirements in air quality management areas.</p><br /><p>The Government is considering future grid and chargepoint requirements as part of its planning for this transition. The UK already has the largest network of rapid chargepoints across Europe and over 6000 publically accessible chargepoints have been part-funded by the Government. We will continue to collaborate with industry to ensure that the UK’s infrastructure network meets the needs of electric vehicle drivers.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","14855","2015-11-10T17:30:02.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426082/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426082/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426082/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-04","Electric Vehicles: Charging Points","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department has assessed the necessary financial support required by local authorities to deliver a charging network for electric vehicles of the scale required to have an effect on local air quality.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","14767"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426083","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-10","<p>As part of a consultation in 2014 on amendments to the Renewable Transport Fuel Obligation (RTFO) the department considered the potential benefits of biopropane in delivering GHG savings. In recognition of this, the Renewable Transport Fuel Obligation was subsequently amended to increase rewards for suppliers of that fuel from April 2015.</p><br /><p>The department, working with the Department for Environment Food and Rural Affairs, have evaluated a range of options for tackling poor air quality; this formed the basis of the Government’s draft air quality plans that recently went to public consultation. Switching to LPG can provide air quality benefits but may not be easily deployed in all vehicle types.</p><br /><p>As part of the department’s 2014 Clean Vehicle Technology Fund (CVTF) grant scheme, Birmingham City Council were awarded £500,000 to enable the conversion of 80 older black cabs from diesel to LPG which will help improve air quality on some of the most polluted roads. There is a possibility of funding through the current CVTF grant scheme being used to support further LPG conversions in other areas.</p><br /><p>We are considering many competing priorities across Government as part of the Spending Review, including measures to tackle air quality pollutants and reduce other harmful emissions. The outcome of the Spending Review will be announced later in the autumn.</p><br /><p>The department regularly meets with motor manufacturers and their representative body the Society of Motor Manufacturers and Traders (SMMT). Discussions on how manufacturers can act to tackle poor air quality cover a range of measures.</p><br />","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","14692 ; 14693 ; 14696","2015-11-10T17:45:45.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426083/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426083/answer",,,,,"