vernment/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/207966/espa.pdf</a>. <br>3. Parliamentary Constituency of claimant (Westminster) these constituencies are used for the Westminster parliament</p><p>4. Information for Northern Ireland is the responsibility of the Department for Social Development. Northern Ireland statistics can be found at:<br><a href="http://www.dsdni.gov.uk/index/stats_and_research/benefit_publications.htm" target="_blank">http://www.dsdni.gov.uk/index/stats_and_research/benefit_publications.htm</a></p><br />","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-11-10T16:03:24.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426151/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426151/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426151/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-04","Carer's Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many women aged (a) 60, (b) 61, (c) 62, (d) 63, (e) 64, (f) 65, (g) 66 and (h) 67 were in receipt of carer's allowance in (i) the UK, (ii) Scotland, (iii) Glasgow and (iv) Glasgow East constituency in the most recent period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Natalie McGarry","Glasgow East","Natalie McGarry","14715"
