ferences.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","14759 ; 14778 ; 14846 ; 14963","2015-11-10T12:34:24.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426176/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426176/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426176/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-04","Motor Vehicles: Exhaust Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many Volkswagen vehicles have been retested for emissions by the Vehicle Certification Agency to date; what the outcome of those retests has been; how many vehicles are still to be retested; and when he expects all retests to be completed.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","14847"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426177","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-10","<p>The Department for Transport (DfT) works collaboratively with Innovate UK through a range of mechanisms to support technological development and innovation in all modes of transport. DfT and Innovate UK work together to support wider government objectives to develop the nation's science and research capability to support UK economic growth. However, the Department has not made any separate assessment of Innovate UK’s contribution to the development of technologies in the transport sector. Innovate UK undertakes well established economic evaluations on the effectiveness and impact of its activities and are reported to the Department for Business Innovation and Skills, as Innovate UK's departmental sponsor.</p><br />","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-11-10T12:48:48.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426177/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426177/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426177/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-04","Transport: Technology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of Innovate UK's contribution to the development of technologies in (a) aviation, (b) road transport and (c) ports and shipping.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","14853"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426178","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-09","<p>Boosting productivity is vital for the UK’s living standards in the long term and the government is committed to tackling the UK’s long history of poor productivity growth. In July the government published “Fixing the foundations: Creating a more prosperous nation” – a 15 point plan for productivity growth in the UK over the next decade.</p><br />","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-11-09T14:46:03.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426178/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426178/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426178/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-04","Productivity","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps he is taking to increase productivity in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","14682"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426179","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-11-09","<p>Access to broadband is of vital importance to small and medium-sized businesses, which is why the Government-funded Broadband Connection Voucher Scheme has provided over 50,000 small and medium sized enterprises with access to high speed broadband.83 per cent of homes and businesses already have access to superfast broadband services, and thanks to the Government's investment in the superfast broadband rollout, this is set to rise to 95 per cent by the end of 2017. In addition, the Government is supportingseven pilot projects exploring options for delivering superfast broadband services to the hardest to reach parts of the UK.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-11-09T15:51:44.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426179/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426179/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426179/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-11-04","Broadband","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he plans to take to improve broadband services in urban areas (a) generally and (b) for small and medium-sized businesses in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","14681"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426180","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-11","<p>Allegations of misuse of the Flexible Support Fund at Plaistow Jobcentre were investigated fully by the Department’s investigators. Disciplinary action was taken in all cases where evidence of the misuse of the Flexible Support Fund was proven.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-11-11T13:15:20.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426180/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426180/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426180/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-04","Jobcentres: Plaistow","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the outcome was of the investigation by his Department's Finance Group Internal Audit and Investigations team into allegations made in December 2013 of inappropriate use of the Flexible Support Fund at Plaistow Jobcentre.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","14920"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426181","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-09","<p>The information requested as to the identity of the authorising officer cannot be shared as it contains personal information relating to third parties.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-11-09T15:15:52.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426181/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426181/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426181/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-04","Jobcentres: Plaistow","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, who authorised the payment from the Flexible Support Fund which led to the dismissal of two staff from Plaistow Jobcentre in May 2014.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","14921"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426182","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-09","<p>Allegations of misuse of the Flexible Support Fund at Plaistow Jobcentre during 2013 and 2014 were investigated fully by the Department’s investigators. Various discussions were held and investigators also undertook further work, completed in July 2014, which examined whether there was a pattern of malpractice or any evidence of wider misuse, of which none was found, of the Flexible Support Fund at this office or other offices in the immediate area.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-11-09T15:28:16.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426182/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426182/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426182/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-04","Jobcentres: Plaistow","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what discussions were held with the two Jobcentre Plus staff dismissed from Plaistow Jobcentre in May 2014 after a complaint about misuse of the Flexible Support Fund on (a) whether that misuse was part of a pattern of malpractice and (b) by whom it was authorised.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","14866"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426183","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-09","<p>The information is not collated centrally. To provide this information could only be done so at disproportionate cost.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-11-09T15:16:22.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426183/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426183/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/426183/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-04","Jobcentres: Plaistow","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many complaints were made by jobseekers about advisers at Plaistow Jobcentre between 1 June 2013 and 31 May 2014.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","14871"
